For concurrent Python specifically: what static patterns indicate unsafe shared state in threading.Thread, asyncio coroutines, and multiprocessing scenarios? How do tools detect unsafe access to shared mutable objects (dicts, lists, class attributes) across threads without synchronisation primitives? What CWE subcategories apply to async race conditions (e.g., asyncio check-then-act)?

Cover commercial and open-source tool capabilities: does Semgrep, CodeQL, Bandit, or any other tool have published rules or queries for Python race condition detection? What do they detect and what are their documented false negative rates? Are there any research tools from academia (2020-2025) specifically targeting Python concurrency bugs?

